OL,3,CWhy did England's Harry Kane have to
OL,4,Cretake penalty against Croatia?
OL,6,FEngland delighted fans with their
OL,7,Fopening World Cup match, defeating
OL,8,FCroatia 4-2 on Wednesday night.
OL,10,FCaptain Harry Kane secured two goals
OL,11,Ffor the Three Lions, before number 10
OL,12,FJude Bellingham and substitute Marcus
OL,13,FRashford secured the team's win in the
OL,14,Fsecond half.
OL,16,FAn early foul in the box on Arsenal
OL,17,Fwinger Noni Madueke by Croatian Luka
OL,18,FModric saw Kane step up to take the
OL,19,Fpenalty kick.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
